Community Science?

How about an organization like <strong><a href="http://www.ub.edu/opensystems/en/site/about/1">OpenSystems</a>,</strong> a multidisciplinary group attached to the University of Barcelona (UB) that focuses on the arts and public participation as core elements of the way of doing science, in Singapore ? With their methodology "based on <strong>community processes</strong> that seek to make <strong>the city and urban environments an open permanent science lab</strong>, although constantly evolving", a new approach for countries to consider so that sustainability is more than just a buzzword.

But so what if the world is divided into proper scientists/researchers and the rest? When the majority of society doesn't understand scientific research (or how stats can be manipulated), media becomes the truth, a recent  : <a href="http://io9.gizmodo.com/i-fooled-millions-into-thinking-chocolate-helps-weight-1707251800">http://io9.gizmodo.com/i-fooled-millions-into-thinking-chocolate-helps-weight-1707251800</a>

