There are 3 streams in The Oxford Doctoral Training Program in Environmental Research: <a href="http://www.environmental-research.ox.ac.uk/researchstream/biodiversity-ecology-and-evolutionary-processes/ ">Biodiversity, Ecology and Evolutionary Processes</a>; <a href="http://www.environmental-research.ox.ac.uk/researchstream/the-dynamic-earth-surface-processes-and-natural-hazards/">The Dynamic Earth, Surface Processes and Natural Hazards</a>; <a href="http://www.environmental-research.ox.ac.uk/researchstream/the-physical-climate-system/">The Physical Climate</a>.

They are now <a title="How To Apply" href="http://www.environmental-research.ox.ac.uk/how-to-apply/">open for applications</a> for entry in October 2015, and expect to offer 24 – 30 four-year DPhil scholarships. The closing date will be 23 January 2015.

